.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH oxiarc-extract 1  "oxiarc-extract " 
.SH NAME
oxiarc\-extract \- Extract files from an archive
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBoxiarc\-extract\fR [\fB\-o\fR|\fB\-\-output\fR] [\fB\-I\fR|\fB\-\-include\fR] [\fB\-X\fR|\fB\-\-exclude\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR] [\fB\-P\fR|\fB\-\-progress\fR] [\fB\-f\fR|\fB\-\-format\fR] [\fB\-\-overwrite\fR] [\fB\-\-skip\-existing\fR] [\fB\-\-prompt\fR] [\fB\-t\fR|\fB\-\-preserve\-timestamps\fR] [\fB\-\-preserve\-permissions\fR] [\fB\-p\fR|\fB\-\-preserve\fR] [\fB\-n\fR|\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR] [\fB\-\-password\fR] [\fB\-\-strict\-names\fR] [\fB\-\-lenient\fR] [\fB\-\-memory\-limit\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIARCHIVE\fR> [\fIFILES\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Extract files from an archive
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-output\fR \fI<OUTPUT>\fR [default: .]
Output directory (use "\-" for stdout when extracting single\-file formats)
.TP
\fB\-I\fR, \fB\-\-include\fR \fI<INCLUDE>\fR
Include only files matching pattern (glob syntax: *.txt, src/**/*)
.TP
\fB\-X\fR, \fB\-\-exclude\fR \fI<EXCLUDE>\fR
Exclude files matching pattern (glob syntax)
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Show verbose output
.TP
\fB\-P\fR, \fB\-\-progress\fR
Show progress bar
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-format\fR \fI<FORMAT>\fR
Format hint for stdin (gzip, xz, bz2, lz4, zst, br, snappy)
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
zip: ZIP archive
.IP \(bu 2
tar: TAR archive
.IP \(bu 2
gzip: GZIP compressed file
.IP \(bu 2
lzh: LZH archive
.IP \(bu 2
xz: XZ compressed file
.IP \(bu 2
lz4: LZ4 compressed file
.IP \(bu 2
bz2: Bzip2 compressed file
.IP \(bu 2
zst: Zstandard compressed file
.IP \(bu 2
br: Brotli compressed file
.IP \(bu 2
snappy: Snappy compressed file
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-overwrite\fR
Always overwrite existing files (default behavior)
.TP
\fB\-\-skip\-existing\fR
Skip extraction if file already exists
.TP
\fB\-\-prompt\fR
Prompt user before overwriting each file
.TP
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-preserve\-timestamps\fR
Preserve file timestamps (modification time)
.TP
\fB\-\-preserve\-permissions\fR
Preserve file permissions (Unix mode)
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-preserve\fR
Preserve all metadata (timestamps and permissions)
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Dry run: show what would be extracted without writing files
.TP
\fB\-\-password\fR \fI<PASSWORD>\fR
Password for encrypted entries (prompts interactively if omitted)
.TP
\fB\-\-strict\-names\fR
Refuse to extract entries whose basename is a Windows reserved name (CON, NUL, COM1.., LPT1..). Default: append \*(Aq_\*(Aq to the stem
.TP
\fB\-\-lenient\fR
Continue on corruption (CRC mismatch, bad TAR checksum, etc.) with warnings instead of errors
.TP
\fB\-\-memory\-limit\fR \fI<MEMORY_LIMIT>\fR
Refuse to extract entries exceeding this memory limit (e.g. 100M, 512K, 1G)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
<\fIARCHIVE\fR>
Archive file to extract (use "\-" for stdin)
.TP
[\fIFILES\fR]
Files to extract (all if empty)
